## üß© 1Ô∏è‚É£ Basic JavaScript Functions (Foundation Level)


## ‚úÖ 1. Basic Built-in Functions

| Function        | Description                           | Example                           |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| `alert()`       | Displays an alert popup               | `alert("Hello!")`                 |
| `prompt()`      | Gets user input                       | `let name = prompt("Your name?")` |
| `confirm()`     | Asks user to confirm (OK/Cancel)      | `confirm("Are you sure?")`        |
| `console.log()` | Prints messages to console            | `console.log("Debugging!")`       |
| `parseInt()`    | Converts string ‚Üí integer             | `parseInt("100")`                 |
| `parseFloat()`  | Converts string ‚Üí float               | `parseFloat("10.55")`             |
| `isNaN()`       | Checks if value is not a number       | `isNaN("abc") // true`            |
| `typeof()`      | Checks variable type                  | `typeof 123 // "number"`          |
| `Number()`      | Converts to number                    | `Number("45") // 45`              |
| `String()`      | Converts to string                    | `String(123) // "123"`            |
| `Boolean()`     | Converts to boolean                   | `Boolean(0) // false`             |
| `eval()`        | Executes string as code (‚ö† dangerous) | `eval("2+2") // 4`                |




### üîπ String Functions

| Function        | Example                                | Purpose                |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `length`        | `"hello".length`                       | String length          |
| `toUpperCase()` | `"js".toUpperCase()` ‚Üí `"JS"`          | Convert to uppercase   |
| `toLowerCase()` | `"JS".toLowerCase()` ‚Üí `"js"`          | Convert to lowercase   |
| `includes()`    | `"hello".includes("he")`               | Check substring        |
| `indexOf()`     | `"hello".indexOf("l")` ‚Üí `2`           | Find position          |
| `slice()`       | `"hello".slice(1, 3)` ‚Üí `"el"`         | Extract part of string |
| `substring()`   | `"hello".substring(1, 3)`              | Extract by index       |
| `replace()`     | `"hi js".replace("js", "world")`       | Replace text           |
| `trim()`        | `" hello ".trim()`                     | Remove spaces          |
| `split()`       | `"a,b,c".split(",")` ‚Üí `["a","b","c"]` | Split string           |
| `charAt()`      | `"hello".charAt(1)` ‚Üí `"e"`            | Character by index     |

