## üì¶ 3Ô∏è‚É£ Array Functions (Most Used in React & Node.js)

| Function      | Example                            | Purpose                   |
| ------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `push()`      | `arr.push(5)`                      | Add to end                |
| `pop()`       | `arr.pop()`                        | Remove from end           |
| `shift()`     | `arr.shift()`                      | Remove first              |
| `unshift()`   | `arr.unshift(0)`                   | Add first                 |
| `concat()`    | `arr1.concat(arr2)`                | Merge arrays              |
| `join()`      | `[1,2,3].join('-')` ‚Üí `"1-2-3"`    | Join elements             |
| `slice()`     | `arr.slice(1,3)`                   | Copy part of array        |
| `splice()`    | `arr.splice(2, 1)`                 | Add/remove elements       |
| `indexOf()`   | `arr.indexOf(2)`                   | Find element index        |
| `includes()`  | `arr.includes(3)`                  | Check existence           |
| `map()`       | `arr.map(x => x*2)`                | Transform array           |
| `filter()`    | `arr.filter(x => x>2)`             | Filter elements           |
| `reduce()`    | `arr.reduce((a,b)=>a+b)`           | Accumulate values         |
| `forEach()`   | `arr.forEach(x => console.log(x))` | Loop through              |
| `find()`      | `arr.find(x => x===2)`             | Find first match          |
| `findIndex()` | `arr.findIndex(x => x===2)`        | Find index                |
| `sort()`      | `arr.sort((a,b)=>a-b)`             | Sort array                |
| `reverse()`   | `arr.reverse()`                    | Reverse array             |
| `every()`     | `arr.every(x => x>0)`              | All true?                 |
| `some()`      | `arr.some(x => x>5)`               | Any true?                 |
| `flat()`      | `[1,[2,3]].flat()`                 | Flatten array             |
| `from()`      | `Array.from("abc")`                | Convert iterable to array |

---

## üß± 4Ô∏è‚É£ Object Functions

| Function           | Example                      | Purpose                        |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `Object.keys()`    | `Object.keys(obj)`           | Get all keys                   |
| `Object.values()`  | `Object.values(obj)`         | Get all values                 |
| `Object.entries()` | `Object.entries(obj)`        | Get key-value pairs            |
| `Object.assign()`  | `Object.assign({}, obj)`     | Copy or merge objects          |
| `hasOwnProperty()` | `obj.hasOwnProperty("name")` | Check key exists               |
| `delete`           | `delete obj.key`             | Remove property                |
| `JSON.stringify()` | `JSON.stringify(obj)`        | Convert to string              |
| `JSON.parse()`     | `JSON.parse(jsonStr)`        | Convert string ‚Üí object        |
| `Object.freeze()`  | `Object.freeze(obj)`         | Make immutable                 |
| `Object.seal()`    | `Object.seal(obj)`           | Lock structure but allow edits |

---

## üïπÔ∏è 5Ô∏è‚É£ Function & Scope Features

| Concept                   | Example                                       | Purpose                   |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `function`                | `function add(a,b){return a+b;}`              | Basic function            |
| **Arrow Function**        | `const add = (a,b)=>a+b`                      | Shorter syntax            |
| **Default Params**        | `function greet(name="User")`                 | Default values            |
| **Rest Operator**         | `function sum(...nums){}`                     | Collect all args          |
| **Spread Operator**       | `const arr=[...arr1,...arr2]`                 | Expand elements           |
| **IIFE**                  | `(()=>{})()`                                  | Run instantly             |
| **Callback**              | `arr.forEach(fn)`                             | Pass function as argument |
| **Closure**               | `function outer(){return function inner(){}}` | Private scope             |
| **Higher-Order Function** | `function(fn){ return fn(); }`                | Function using functions  |

---

## ‚è≥ 6Ô∏è‚É£ Date & Time Functions

| Function        | Example                  | Purpose                |
| --------------- | ------------------------ | ---------------------- |
| `new Date()`    | `new Date()`             | Create date object     |
| `getFullYear()` | `date.getFullYear()`     | Get year               |
| `getMonth()`    | `date.getMonth()`        | 0‚Äì11 month             |
| `getDate()`     | `date.getDate()`         | Day of month           |
| `getDay()`      | `date.getDay()`          | 0‚Äì6 (Sunday‚ÄìSaturday)  |
| `getHours()`    | `date.getHours()`        | 0‚Äì23 hours             |
| `setFullYear()` | `date.setFullYear(2025)` | Change year            |
| `toISOString()` | `date.toISOString()`     | Standard format        |
| `Date.now()`    | `Date.now()`             | Current timestamp (ms) |

---

## ‚ö° 7Ô∏è‚É£ Promise & Async Functions (Modern JS)

| Function          | Example                      | Purpose            |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------ |
| `Promise`         | `new Promise((res,rej)=>{})` | Async control      |
| `then()`          | `promise.then(res=>{})`      | Handle success     |
| `catch()`         | `promise.catch(err=>{})`     | Handle error       |
| `finally()`       | `promise.finally(()=>{})`    | Always run         |
| `async/await`     | `await fetch()`              | Wait for async ops |
| `Promise.all()`   | `Promise.all([p1,p2])`       | Wait all           |
| `Promise.race()`  | `Promise.race([p1,p2])`      | First to finish    |
| `setTimeout()`    | `setTimeout(()=>{},1000)`    | Delay execution    |
| `setInterval()`   | `setInterval(()=>{},1000)`   | Repeat every X ms  |
| `clearTimeout()`  | `clearTimeout(timer)`        | Stop timeout       |
| `clearInterval()` | `clearInterval(timer)`       | Stop interval      |

---

## üß© 8Ô∏è‚É£ DOM Functions (Browser Side)

| Function                    | Example                            | Purpose         |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------- | --------------- |
| `document.getElementById()` | `getElementById("id")`             | Get element     |
| `document.querySelector()`  | `querySelector(".class")`          | CSS selector    |
| `querySelectorAll()`        | `querySelectorAll("div")`          | Get all matches |
| `createElement()`           | `document.createElement("div")`    | Make element    |
| `appendChild()`             | `parent.appendChild(child)`        | Add to DOM      |
| `removeChild()`             | `parent.removeChild(child)`        | Remove from DOM |
| `innerHTML`                 | `el.innerHTML = "<p>Hello</p>"`    | Insert HTML     |
| `textContent`               | `el.textContent = "Hello"`         | Insert text     |
| `addEventListener()`        | `el.addEventListener("click", fn)` | Add event       |
| `classList.add()`           | `el.classList.add("active")`       | Add class       |
| `classList.remove()`        | `el.classList.remove("active")`    | Remove class    |

---

## üß† 9Ô∏è‚É£ Advanced / Modern JS Concepts (Must Know)

| Concept                                | Description                   |
| -------------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Destructuring (`{name} = obj`)         | Extract values easily         |
| Template literals (`` `Hi ${name}` ``) | Embedded variables in strings |
| Modules (`import/export`)              | Split code into files         |
| Optional chaining (`obj?.prop`)        | Safe property access          |
| Nullish coalescing (`??`)              | Fallback if null/undefined    |
| Generators (`function*`)               | Pause/resume functions        |
| Iterators                              | Custom looping behavior       |
| Currying                               | `f(a)(b)` style function      |
| Debounce / Throttle                    | Optimize events               |
| Fetch API                              | Modern AJAX replacement       |
| LocalStorage / SessionStorage          | Save browser data             |
| Event Loop / Microtasks                | JS concurrency model          |
| Prototypes / Classes                   | Object-oriented JS            |
| this / bind / call / apply             | Function context control      |

---

## üöÄ 10Ô∏è‚É£ Utility / Misc Functions

| Function                      | Example                    | Purpose                     |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| `typeof`                      | `typeof "Hi"` ‚Üí `"string"` | Check data type             |
| `instanceof`                  | `arr instanceof Array`     | Check class type            |
| `isArray()`                   | `Array.isArray([])`        | Check if array              |
| `eval()`                      | `eval("2+2")`              | Evaluate JS code (‚ö†Ô∏è avoid) |
| `encodeURI()` / `decodeURI()` | Encode/decode URLs         |                             |
| `btoa()` / `atob()`           | Base64 encode/decode       |                             |

